      "content": "i mean i get there's different theories, but isn't it kind of obvious that the \"dangerous\" side is usually what we see in history? like, if you look at the 20th century, nationalism is pretty much the root of most of the world's biggest conflicts. it feels like the \"necessary for cohesion\" argument is just a way to justify bad stuff. wouldn't it be more accurate to say that nationalism is fundamentally a problem?",
